content.text:
Let me analyze the structure and provide assembly instructions.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure appears to be a rectangular frame made of yellow and green blocks
- It consists of 4 blocks in total
- The frame has green blocks at the top and bottom, with yellow blocks forming the vertical sides

Block Count and Layers:
- Total blocks: 4
- Layers: Can be built from bottom up in 3 layers

Required Blocks from Dictionary:
1. Bottom: Green horizontal block (Block #2)
2. Middle: Two yellow vertical blocks (Block #9 or #10) for sides
3. Top: Green horizontal block (Block #2)

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 2 (Place green horizontal block at bottom)
    Step2: Move block with index 9 (Place yellow vertical block on left side)
    Step3: Move block with index 9 (Place yellow vertical block on right side)
    Step4: Move block with index 2 (Place green horizontal block at top)
}

This will create the rectangular frame structure shown in the target image, with green blocks forming the top and bottom horizontal pieces and yellow blocks forming the vertical sides.
